Hi,<P>

My name is Ana Cordova. I am an MS/PhD student in the Natural Resource
Policy and Management program at Cornell University. I am currently studying
the viability of stakeholder involvement in natural resource decision-making
in the Copper Canyon region of Chihuahua, Mexico (Sierra Madre Occidental
Mountain Range). Citizen/public involvement is particularly relevant at this
moment, where various government agencies are independently proposing
different regional plans for this area (Tourism Master Plan, Sustainable
Forestry Plan, a possible Protected Area) and could perhaps benefit from
input from a wide range of stakeholders.<P>

This is the first time I am participating in an electronic discussion group. <P>
 
Ana.<P>


